This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with image segmentation using electron microscopy. The use of a novel agglomerative framework also suggests that it could fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The proposed delayed scheme for agglomerative clustering could also indicate a potential fit for the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category. Finally, the mention of 2D and 3D datasets suggests that this paper could also be relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) category.
